articles.author: Maha Dahan, Olesya Astakhova
articles.description: Top oil exporters Saudi Arabia and Russia confirmed on Sunday they would continue with their additional voluntary oil output cuts until the end of the year as concerns over demand and economic growth continue to weigh on crude markets.
articles.title: Saudi Arabia, Russia to continue additional voluntary oil cuts

articles.author: Tetsushi Kajimoto
articles.description: Most Bank of Japan board members saw no need for additional tweaks to yield curve control and agreed to continued monetary easing to meet inflation and wage growth objectives, minutes of its September meeting showed on Monday.
articles.title: Bank of Japan members saw no need for new yield control tweaks, September minutes show

articles.author: Julia Payne
articles.description: A major pharmaceutical rules overhaul, proposed by the European Commission in April, could see Europe's share in global research and development contract by a third to 21% by 2040 translating to 2 billion euros ($2.15 billion) per year in lost investment, industry group EFPIA said on Monday.
articles.title: EU proposal may accelerate pharma innovation decline, industry group says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ant Group has received Chinese government approval to release products powered by its "Bailing" artificial intelligence (AI) large language model to the public, a spokesperson for the Chinese firm said on Monday.
articles.title: Ant Group wins approval to release AI products to Chinese public

articles.author: Simon Jessop
articles.description: Half of the world's 2,000 biggest listed companies have set a target to get to net-zero emissions by mid-century, but just a fraction meet tough United Nations guidelines for what constitutes a quality pledge, a report on Monday showed.
articles.title: Just 4% of top companies meet UN climate target guidelines, study says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Japan's services activity expanded at the slowest pace this year in October, a business survey showed on Monday, reinforcing concerns that the key sector propelling economic growth is continuing to soften.
articles.title: Japan service activity posts slowest growth this year - PMI

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Superannuation fund AustralianSuper has raised its stake in power producer Origin Energy (ORG.AX) to 15.03%, cementing its position as the company's largest shareholder, an exchange filing on Monday showed.
articles.title: AustralianSuper raises stake in Origin Energy; will not join Brookfield consortium

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Efforts to pressure Israel to spare civilians in Gaza were set to continue on Monday after Israel rebuffed calls for a ceasefire amid a U.S. diplomatic blitz to the region to help contain escalation of the conflict.
articles.title: Pressure on Israel over civilians steps up as ceasefire calls rebuffed

articles.author: Max Hunder
articles.description: In Ukraine's war-ravaged Donetsk region, soldiers dug in near the front line described how Russian artillery had intensified significantly in recent weeks, but said it remains below peaks seen a year ago as both sides struggle to advance.
articles.title: Near Donetsk front line, Ukraine artillery crew face intensifying fire

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Elon Musk's artificial intelligence startup xAI will be integrated into his social media platform X and also be available as a standalone app, he said on Sunday in a post.
articles.title: Musk to integrate xAI with social media platform X
